      "date": "2011-05-17 18:06:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAndreas, the change made obviously works. But given this feature was added for one bug and that bug is now gone can we not remove the whole of SKIP_LFSCK from the two files in this review..\n\nI guess that some people might say this is a feature and should be left,but actually it's just the ability to have the test scripts behave in a random way because of a global variable set in a script far far away.",
